{"serial": "41037", "department_serial": 38, "code": "BA7082", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Digital Transformation", "ch": "數位轉型"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Chen, Shiuann-Shuoh"], "ch": ["陳炫碩"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 2, "session": ["A", "B", "C"]}, "loc": {"building": "I1", "room": "018"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "企業管理學系", "en": "Department of Business Administration"}, "system": {"ch": "碩博同修", "en": "Master/Doctoral Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 31, "selected": 48, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "數位技術進步隨之而來的消費型態，市場結構，營運模式的改變，對現代企業產生極大的衝擊，本課程以近來發展趨勢為主軸，探討企業如何利用數位技術在產品發展、客戶開發以及經營模式方面順利轉型。", "en": "數位技術進步隨之而來的消費型態，市場結構，營運模式的改變，對現代企業產生極大的衝擊，本課程以近來發展趨勢為主軸，探討企業如何利用數位技術在產品發展、客戶開發以及經營模式方面順利轉型。"}, "outline": {"ch": "\"1  數位經濟的特色\n2  客戶社群\n3  數位行銷\n4  行動支付\n5  平台經濟\n6  平台建立\n7  平台營運\n8  數據資產\n9  期中考\n10  物聯網營運模式\n11  數位內容\n12  長尾效應\n13\nNetflix (9-607-133)(Chinese Version: 610-C04)\nWould you have been long or short Blockbuster stock at the time of the case?  How about Netflix?  Why?\nDid Netflix do the same jobs for consumers that Blockbuster did?  How did this evolve over time?\nCompare Blockbuster’s and Netflix’s profit models.  How might the differences affect the respective company’s strategies?\nAs you examine each major shift in Netflix’s strategy, what might have been an assumptions checklist that they might have used at each stage?  What assumptions checklist might you use for VOD?\n14\nUber: Changing the way the world moves (9-316-101)\nDo you agree or disagree with Uber’s surge pricing policy? What are the reasons it can be perceived as unfair? What are the risks of the policy to Uber? Given these risks, Should Uber modify its policy?\nUber has become enormously popular among consumer in a very short period of time.  How has the company accomplished this?\nHow robust is Uber’s operating model?  What are the weak links for its service model?\n15\nOnline Restaurant Promotion (9-909-034)\nWhat are the key success factors for each business model?\nIf you had to invest in one of these businesses, which would you choose? Why?\nWho pays for these restaurant promotion services?\n16 Mednet.com (2066)\nWhat does an advertiser want? Sales, leads, brand awareness?\nWhat specific consumer behaviors determine whether or not a business model produces the results an advertiser wants? What are the best metrics for measuring these?\nWhat is the best argument Heather yates can make to justify charging Windham Pharmaceuticals for impressions instead of click-throughs?  Does she have acceptable alternatives?\nWhat value to the customer does a general interest site contribute that a niche site can’t?\nWhat steps can MedNet take to address emerging competitive threats?\n17\nApple Pay (8-516-027)\nWill Apple Pay be a huge success with consumers? Why or why not? ?\nWhy did banks agree to partner with Apple for Apple Pay in the U.S.? ?\nAre retailers excited about Apple Pay? Why or why not? ?\nWhat is Apple’s motivation in launching Apple Pay?\nShould Apple make any changes to its Apple Pay roll-out plan?\n18 期末考\"", "en": "\"1. Digital Economy\n2. Customer Network\n3. Digital Marketing\n4. Mobile Payment\n5. Platform Economy\n6. Platform Mobilization\n7. Platform Management\n8. Data Asset\n9. Mid-Term\n10. IOT Business Model\n11. Digital Content\n12. Long Tail\n13\nNetflix (9-607-133)(Chinese Version: 610-C04)\nWould you have been long or short Blockbuster stock at the time of the case?  How about Netflix?  Why?\nDid Netflix do the same jobs for consumers that Blockbuster did?  How did this evolve over time?\nCompare Blockbuster’s and Netflix’s profit models.  How might the differences affect the respective company’s strategies?\nAs you examine each major shift in Netflix’s strategy, what might have been an assumptions checklist that they might have used at each stage?  What assumptions checklist might you use for VOD?\n14\nUber: Changing the way the world moves (9-316-101)\nDo you agree or disagree with Uber’s surge pricing policy? What are the reasons it can be perceived as unfair? What are the risks of the policy to Uber? Given these risks, Should Uber modify its policy?\nUber has become enormously popular among consumer in a very short period of time.  How has the company accomplished this?\nHow robust is Uber’s operating model?  What are the weak links for its service model?\n15\nOnline Restaurant Promotion (9-909-034)\nWhat are the key success factors for each business model?\nIf you had to invest in one of these businesses, which would you choose? Why?\nWho pays for these restaurant promotion services?\n16 Mednet.com (2066)\nWhat does an advertiser want? Sales, leads, brand awareness?\nWhat specific consumer behaviors determine whether or not a business model produces the results an advertiser wants? What are the best metrics for measuring these?\nWhat is the best argument Heather yates can make to justify charging Windham Pharmaceuticals for impressions instead of click-throughs?  Does she have acceptable alternatives?\nWhat value to the customer does a general interest site contribute that a niche site can’t?\nWhat steps can MedNet take to address emerging competitive threats?\n17\nApple Pay (8-516-027)\nWill Apple Pay be a huge success with consumers? Why or why not? ?\nWhy did banks agree to partner with Apple for Apple Pay in the U.S.? ?\nAre retailers excited about Apple Pay? Why or why not? ?\nWhat is Apple’s motivation in launching Apple Pay?\nShould Apple make any changes to its Apple Pay roll-out plan?\n18. Final\""}, "textbook": {"ch": "\"自編教材\n哈佛商學院個案\"", "en": "\"自編教材\n哈佛商學院個案\""}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "100", "en": "100"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "\"class participation 40%\ninterview 20%\npresentation 40%\"", "en": "\"cla